The families of Gabby Petito and Brian Laundrie released statements Tuesday, both expressing their hopes for Gabrielle's safe return, but with critical details still missing.

A statement from the family of Brian Laundrie says the Laundrie family hopes the search for Gabby is "successful." Gabby Petito's family responded, calling for Laundrie to tell them where he last saw Gabby.

"Brian [Laundrie] is refusing to tell Gabby's family where he last saw her. Brian is also refusing to explain why he left Gabby all alone and drove her van to Florida. These are critical questions that require immediate answers," the family's statement said, in part. 

More: https://www.fox13news.com/news/gabby-petito-disappearance-boyfriend-located-with-van-at-north-port-family-home
